<LegalLayout lang="en" title="Cookie Policy" lastUpdated="2026-07-18">

## 1. What are cookies

Cookies are small text files stored on your device when you visit a website. They help the site remember your preferences and improve your experience.

## 2. How we use cookies

This website uses **minimal cookies** and prioritizes your privacy:

### 2.1 Essential cookies (no consent required)
- **Session cookies:** Required for the website to function properly. These are temporary and deleted when you close your browser.

### 2.2 Analytics (no consent required)
We use **Plausible Analytics**, which is **fully cookieless**. Plausible does not set any cookies on your device. It processes page views anonymously and is compliant with GDPR, CCPA, and PECR without requiring a cookie consent banner.

### 2.3 Third-party services
When you interact with third-party services embedded on our site, those services may set their own cookies:
- **Calendly** — when you open the scheduling modal, Calendly may set functional cookies
- **Cloudflare Worker + Resend** — form submissions are processed server-side without cookies
- **LinkedIn, Instagram, WhatsApp** — if you click external links, those platforms may set cookies per their own policies

## 3. What we do NOT do

- We do **not** use advertising or tracking cookies
- We do **not** sell or share your personal data with advertisers
- We do **not** use fingerprinting or cross-site tracking
- We do **not** require a cookie consent banner (because we don't use tracking cookies)

## 4. Managing cookies

Since we don't use tracking cookies, there is nothing to manage. If you prefer to block all cookies (including essential ones), you can configure your browser settings. Note that this may affect the basic functionality of the website.

## 5. Changes to this policy

We may update this policy from time to time. The "Last updated" date at the top indicates the most recent revision.

## 6. Contact

For cookie-related inquiries, contact us at contact@flintlockagency.com.

